St._Paul.Burbank\u2013Livingston\u2013Griggs Hous: The Burbank–Livingston–Griggs House is one of the first examples of Italianate or Tuscan order architecture in Saint Paul in the U.S. state of Minnesota. The house, located at 432 Summit Avenue is listed on the National Register of Historic Places. It is also a contributing property to the Historic Hill District.
